<taxonomicName id="7EE386B39C5A2A10EFC15A5AFE5F595F" authority="Rambur, 1842" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[151,473,1125,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Megistopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10EFC15A5AFE5F595F" bold="true" box="[151,473,1125,1151]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10EFC15A5AFEA7595F" bold="true" box="[151,289,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Megistopus</emphasis>
Rambur, 1842
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F1F9AEBB9C5A2A10EFC15A93FB805875" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B95CFD309C5A2A10EFC15A93FCF95811" blockId="34.[151,1436,1196,1653]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10EFC15A93FE9759E5" bold="true" box="[151,273,1196,1221]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Mandibles comparatively long, equipped with 3 pairs of teeth; pronotum covered by long setae; mesothoracic spiracles pronounced, raised on tubercle; thoracic setiferous processes pedunculated; odontoid processes of the VIII sternite atrophied or completely absent; IX sternite with rastra bearing 4 pairs of digging setae of which the internal pair is not over a quarter the others in length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B95CFD309C5A2A10EF915B03FB805875" blockId="34.[151,1436,1196,1653]" box="[199,1030,1340,1365]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10EF915B03FE275875" bold="true" box="[199,417,1340,1365]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Examined species.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="7EE386B39C5A2A10EEF15B02FD635875" authority="(Rossi, 1790)" baseAuthorityName="Rossi" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[423,741,1340,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Megistopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicornis">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10EEF15B02FDC25875" box="[423,580,1340,1365]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">M. flavicornis</emphasis>
(Rossi, 1790)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7EE386B39C5A2A10EDA65B02FB845875" authority="(Navas, 1912)" baseAuthorityName="Navas" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[752,1026,1340,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Megistopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucasi">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10EDA65B02FCDE5875" box="[752,856,1340,1365]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">M. lucasi</emphasis>
(Navás, 1912)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F1F9AEBB9C5A2A10EF915B5FFA8B5B55" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B95CFD309C5A2A10EF915B5FFA8B5B55" blockId="34.[151,1436,1196,1653]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10EF915B5FFEC95859" bold="true" box="[199,335,1376,1401]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Comments.</emphasis>
An exclusively western Palaearctic genus, 
<taxonomicName id="7EE386B39C5A2A10EC115B5EFC4E5858" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[839,968,1377,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Megistopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10EC115B5EFC4E5858" box="[839,968,1377,1400]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Megistopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises 3 species: the widespread 
<taxonomicName id="7EE386B39C5A2A10EA2B5B5EFE3058BD" authority="(Rossi, 1790)" baseAuthorityName="Rossi" baseAuthorityYear="1790" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Megistopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicornis">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10EA2B5B5EFE8958BD" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">M. flavicornis</emphasis>
(Rossi, 1790)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7EE386B39C5A2A10EE935BBAFC8158BD" authority="(Holzel, 1980)" baseAuthorityName="Holzel" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[453,775,1412,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Megistopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10EE935BBAFDD558BD" box="[453,595,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">M. mirabilis</emphasis>
(Hölzel, 1980)
</taxonomicName>
, known for a single specimen from Sinai and finally 
<taxonomicName id="7EE386B39C5A2A10EA2B5BBAFE0458E1" authority="(Navas, 1912)" baseAuthorityName="Navas" baseAuthorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Megistopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucasi">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10EA2B5BBAFF5C58E1" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">M. lucasi</emphasis>
(Navás, 1912)
</taxonomicName>
reported from 
<collectingCountry id="C1F4BDA09C5A2A10ED795B97FD0558E1" box="[559,643,1448,1473]" name="Algeria" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Algeria</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="C1F4BDA09C5A2A10EDEA5B97FC8958E1" box="[700,783,1448,1473]" name="Tunisia" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
(H. 
<bibRefCitation id="DD7280C19C5A2A10EC135B97FB9958E1" author="Aspock, H. &amp; Holzel, H. &amp; Aspock, U." box="[837,1055,1448,1473]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 606" refId="ref38463" refString="Aspock, H., Holzel, H. &amp; Aspock, U. (2001) Kommentierter Katalog der Neuropterida (Insecta: Raphidioptera, Megaloptera, Neuroptera) der Westpalaarktis. Denisia, 2, 1 - 606." type="journal article" year="2001">
Aspöck 
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10ECF55B96FC5258E1" box="[931,980,1448,1473]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. 2001
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="DD7280C19C5A2A10EB7B5B97FB4458E1" author="Gusten, R." box="[1069,1218,1448,1473]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="129 - 149" refId="ref39916" refString="Gusten, R. (2003) A checklist and new species records of Neuropterida (Insecta) from Tunisia. Kaupia, 12, 129 - 149." type="journal article" year="2003">Güsten 2003</bibRefCitation>
). The latter species was overlooked for a considerable time, being originally described as a member of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="7EE386B39C5A2A10EBEA5BF3FA1A58C5" authority="Navas, 1912" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1912" box="[1212,1436,1484,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Nelees" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10EBEA5BF3FA8158C5" box="[1212,1287,1484,1509]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Nelees</emphasis>
Navás, 1912
</taxonomicName>
(now synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="7EE386B39C5A2A10EE305BCFFDF55B29" authority="Navas, 1909" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1909" box="[358,627,1520,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Neuroleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10EE305BCFFE5D5B29" box="[358,475,1520,1545]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Neuroleon</emphasis>
Navás, 1909
</taxonomicName>
), despite the correct genus placement was already recognized by 
<bibRefCitation id="DD7280C19C5A2A10EA005BCFFF635B0D" author="Banks, N." pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="149 - 157" refId="ref38711" refString="Banks, N. (1913) Notes on African Myrmeleonidae. Journal of the New York Entomological Society, 21, 149 - 157. [Bernardi] Iori, A., Kathirithamby, J., Letardi, A., Pantaleoni, R. A. &amp; Principi, M. M. (1995) 62. Neuropteroidea (Megaloptera, Raphidioptera, Planipennia), Mecoptera, Siphonaptera, Strepsiptera. In: Minelli, A., Ruffo, S. &amp; La Posta, S. (Eds.), Checklist delle specie animali italiane. Calderini Editore, Bologna, 20 pp." type="book chapter" year="1913">Banks (1913)</bibRefCitation>
. This interesting species is also present in 
<collectingCountry id="C1F4BDA09C5A2A10ED8F582BFC8A5B0D" box="[729,780,1556,1581]" name="Italy" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Italy</collectingCountry>
([Bernardi] Iori 
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10EC87582AFB8B5B0D" box="[977,1037,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al.</emphasis>
1995; 
<bibRefCitation id="DD7280C19C5A2A10EB37582BFA115B0D" author="Letardi, A. &amp; Pantaleoni, R. A." box="[1121,1431,1556,1581]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="277 - 305" refId="ref40373" refString="Letardi, A. &amp; Pantaleoni, R. A. (1996) Neurotteri W-paleartici del Museo di Zoologia di Roma (Insecta Neuropteroidea). Fragmenta Entomologica, 28, 277 - 305." type="journal article" year="1996">Letardi &amp; Pantaleoni 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="DD7280C19C5A2A10EFC15807FE295B71" author="Letardi, A. &amp; Maltzeff, P." box="[151,431,1592,1617]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="49 - 62" refId="ref40329" refString="Letardi, A. &amp; Maltzeff, P. (2001) Neurotteridi e Mecotteri della Tenuta Presidenziale di Castelporziano e delle aree limitrofe (Neuroptera, Raphidioptera, Mecoptera). Bollettino dell'Associazione Romana di Entomologia, 54, 49 - 62." type="journal article" year="2001">Letardi &amp; Maltzeff 2001</bibRefCitation>
), although the Italian specimens were originally assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="7EE386B39C5A2A10EB035806FB595B71" baseAuthorityName="Holzel" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[1109,1247,1592,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Megistopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10EB035806FB595B71" box="[1109,1247,1592,1617]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">M. mirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The larva of 
<taxonomicName id="7EE386B39C5A2A10EA2B5806FE895B55" baseAuthorityName="Rossi" baseAuthorityYear="1790" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Megistopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicornis">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10EA2B5806FE895B55" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">M. flavicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only species of the genus whose larva is known (
<bibRefCitation id="DD7280C19C5A2A10EC2D5863FB895B55" author="Steffan, J. R." box="[891,1039,1628,1653]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="693 - 707" refId="ref42381" refString="Steffan, J. R. (1965) Les larves de Megistopus flavicornis (Rossi), Creoleon lugduense (Villers), Neuroleon ocreatus (Navas) et N. nemausiensis (Borkh.) (Planipennes, Myrmeleontidae). Vie et Milieu, 15, 693 - 707." type="journal article" year="1965">Steffan 1965</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="DD7280C19C5A2A10EB4C5863FA875B55" author="Cesaroni, C. &amp; Nicoli Aldini, R. &amp; Pantaleoni, R. A." box="[1050,1281,1628,1653]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="135 - 144" refId="ref39087" refString="Cesaroni, C., Nicoli Aldini, R. &amp; Pantaleoni, R. A. (2010) The larvae of Gymnocnemia variegata (Schneider, 1845) and Megistopus flavicornis (Rossi, 1790) (Neuroptera: Myrmeleontidae): a comparative description. In: Devetak, D., Lipovsek, S., Arnett, A. E. (Eds.), Proceedings of the 10 th International Symposium on Neuropterology (22 - 25 June 2008, Piran, Slovenia). University of Maribor, Maribor, Slovenia, pp. 135 - 144." type="book chapter" year="2010">
Cesaroni 
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5A2A10EBD35862FB305B55" box="[1157,1206,1628,1653]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
